---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Supabase setup required">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-xl py-16 px-4">
    <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold">Supabase isn't configured yet</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-ink-muted">
      Lessons and practice quizzes still work in this dev session — but
      accounts, progress tracking, and the dashboard need a Supabase project.
    </p>
    <ol class="mt-6 list-decimal space-y-3 pl-5 text-sm">
      <li>Create a project at <a class="text-accent underline" href="https://supabase.com">supabase.com</a> (free tier is fine).</li>
      <li>Copy <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5">.env.example</code> to <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5">.env</code> and paste your project URL + anon key.</li>
      <li>Open the SQL editor and run <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5">supabase/schema.sql</code>.</li>
      <li>Restart the dev server: <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5">npm run dev</code>.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="mt-8">
      <a class="text-accent underline" href="/">← Back to lessons</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
